  reasonDescriptions:
    m_Keys: 
    m_Values:
    - Reason has not been set.
    - The object is empty (has no visible content), so it was skipped.
    - "The object is manually tagged as image (e.g. with the \u2018img\u2019 tag),
      so child components are ignored."
    - The vector is at the root of the frame, so it is recognized as a single image.
    - "Button transition type is \u2018SpriteSwapForAll\u2019, so the button child
      is forced as a downloadable image."
    - The object contains an icon child, so it is forced as a container.
    - Object has custom button tags and its child tree allows single image, so it
      is treated as a downloadable image.
    - "The object\u2019s child tree contains only vectors/non-UI elements, recognized
      as a single image."
    - The object is a Figma boolean operation, treated as a single image.
    - The object has visible children, treated as a container.
    - No specific condition matched, so the object cannot be inside a single image
      (default behavior).
    - The object is forced as a container, cannot be inside a single image.
    - Object is already forced as an image, so it is not merged into a parent single
      image.
    - "Since this object contains the tags \u2018{0}\u2019, its parent cannot be
      a single sprite."
    - "This object\u2019s tags do not prevent setting the parent as a single sprite;
      however, if you see this message, other objects in the hierarchy are preventing
      it."
    - "The object is empty \u2014 not downloadable."
    - "Manually tagged as image \u2014 always downloadable."
    - "The object is a Figma vector \u2014 always downloadable."
    - "The object is used as a mask \u2014 always downloadable."
    - "The object doesn\u2019t have the Image tag \u2014 not downloadable."
    - "One of the object\u2019s tags prevents downloading."
    - "The object has arc data (e.g. pie chart) \u2014 always downloadable."
    - "Contains an image, emoji, or video fill \u2014 always downloadable."
    - "Fill with transparency + stroke \u2014 must be downloaded as image."
    - "Object smaller than 48px with outside stroke \u2014 must be downloaded."
    - "Multiple visible fills \u2014 must be downloaded."
    - "Multiple visible strokes \u2014 must be downloaded."
    - "Both fill and stroke present \u2014 must be downloaded."
    - Both fill and stroke are present, but the current procedural component (MPUIKit/FlexibleImage)
      supports rendering them without downloading.
    - No fills or strokes found.
    - "Gradients unsupported by current framework \u2014 must be downloaded."
    - The gradient type used in this object is supported by the selected image component,
      so it will be rendered procedurally instead of downloading.
    - "Not a rectangle shape \u2014 must be downloaded."
    - "Has rounded corners \u2014 must be downloaded."
    - "Has visible strokes \u2014 must be downloaded."
    - Gradient fill + stroke unsupported by procedural component.
    - "Has shadow effects \u2014 must be downloaded."
    - "Has blur effects \u2014 must be downloaded."
    - "No downloadable condition was matched \u2014 the object is not downloadable."
    - "SVG image component is used \u2014 generation not needed."
    - "Procedural image component is used \u2014 generation not needed."
    - "UI Toolkit framework is used \u2014 generation not needed."
    - "Nova framework is used \u2014 generation not needed."
    - "The object is downloadable \u2014 generation not needed."
    - "Overlapped by a stroke \u2014 generation not applicable."
    - "The object\u2019s render size exceeds the maximum allowed for sprite generation."
    - "Not a rectangle \u2014 cannot be generated."
    - "Has both fill and stroke \u2014 cannot be generated."
    - The object has only a stroke (no fill), so a sprite can be generated for it.
    - The object has rounded corners, so a sprite can be generated for it.
    - "Sprite generation failed at runtime \u2014 fallback to Drawable."
    - Object mask applied via Nova ClipMask with sprite texture.
    - Object mask applied via Unity Mask component (showMaskGraphic=false).
    - Object mask not supported in SpriteRenderer mode.
    - Frame/clip mask applied via Nova ClipMask.
    - Frame/clip mask applied via Unity Mask (linear material or rotated object).
    - Frame/clip mask applied via RectMask2D.
    - Frame/clip mask not supported in SpriteRenderer mode.
    - Solid fill color applied directly to the image component.
    - Gradient fill rendered natively by the image component (FlexibleImage only).
    - Gradient fill applied via an external DAGradient component, since the image
      component does not support gradients natively.
    - "No fill present \u2014 the object is in stroke-only mode, so the fill color
      is set to transparent."
    - "Fill is baked into the downloaded or generated sprite \u2014 no additional
      color processing needed."
    - "Sprite has a single dominant color \u2014 applied as a tint to reduce texture
      memory usage."
    - Stroke rendered natively by the image component (Shapes2D outlineSize, MPUIKit
      OutlineWidth, FlexibleImage outline).
    - "Stroke applied via Unity Outline component \u2014 used for OUTSIDE stroke
      alignment when the image component does not support it natively."
    - Stroke applied via SpriteOutline component (SpriteRenderer mode only).
    - Stroke rendered as procedural border width (JoshPUI BorderWidth, DttPUI BorderThickness)
      in stroke-only mode.
    - "Stroke is baked into the downloaded or generated sprite \u2014 no additional
      stroke processing needed."
    - "Stroke alignment (CENTER or INSIDE) is not supported by the current image
      component \u2014 stroke was ignored and removed."
    - "No stroke processing needed \u2014 the object has no visible strokes."
    - 9-slice plugin structure detected and applied successfully.
    - "The object has no children \u2014 cannot apply 9-slice plugin structure."
    - The object does not have exactly 9 child elements required for 9-slice.
    - The child elements do not have the correct anchor positions for 9-slice.
    - "Auto 9-slice applied \u2014 sprite borders set from rounded corners."
    - "The object has no rounded corners \u2014 auto 9-slice not applicable."
    - "The object is not a rectangle \u2014 auto 9-slice not applicable."
    - "The object has multiple colors or gradients \u2014 auto 9-slice not applicable."
    - The object has effects (shadow, blur) incompatible with auto 9-slice.
    - "The object has children \u2014 auto 9-slice not applicable."
    - "The object is a Figma vector \u2014 tagged as Image."
    - "The object has visible fills \u2014 tagged as Image."
    - "The object has visible strokes \u2014 tagged as Image."
    - The object is recognized as a background element.
    - "The object is a Figma boolean operation \u2014 treated as a single Image."
    - "The object\u2019s children contain only vectors \u2014 merged into a single
      Image."
    - "The object is manually tagged as image (e.g. with the \u2018img\u2019 tag)."
    - "The vector is at the root of the frame \u2014 recognized as Image."
    - The object has button tags and can be rendered as a single Image.
    - "Button transition uses SpriteSwapForAll \u2014 child forced as Image."
    - "The object has visible children \u2014 tagged as Container."
    - "The object contains an icon child \u2014 forced as Container."
    - The object is manually forced as a Container.
    - "The parent is a Page \u2014 the object is tagged as Frame."
    - "The Figma node type is TEXT \u2014 tagged as Text."
    - "The object has a Figma Auto Layout mode \u2014 tagged as AutoLayoutGroup."
    - "Text has auto-resize enabled (Height or WidthAndHeight) \u2014 tagged as ContentSizeFitter."
    - "The object has \u2018Preserve Ratio\u2019 enabled \u2014 tagged as AspectRatioFitter."
    - "The object is a Figma mask or has clip content \u2014 tagged as Mask."
    - "The object name matches button naming convention \u2014 tagged as Button."
    - "The object has shadow effects \u2014 tagged as Shadow."
    - "The object has background blur \u2014 tagged as Blur."
    - "The object has layout grids \u2014 tagged as LayoutGrid."
    - "The object opacity is not 1.0 \u2014 tagged as CanvasGroup."
    - "The object has a valid 9-slice plugin structure \u2014 tagged as Slice9."
    - "The object passed auto 9-slice checks \u2014 tagged as AutoSlice9."
    - The object name contains a manual Figma tag (e.g. btn-default).
    - "Parent is not a Page \u2014 Frame tag not assigned."
    - "Object has no Auto Layout mode (HORIZONTAL/VERTICAL/WRAP) \u2014 AutoLayoutGroup
      not assigned."
    - "Object has Auto Layout mode but no visible children \u2014 AutoLayoutGroup
      not assigned."
    - "PreserveRatio is not enabled on this object \u2014 AspectRatioFitter not assigned."
    - "Object is not a Figma mask and does not have clip content \u2014 Mask not
      assigned."
    - "Object name is not \"button\" \u2014 Button tag not assigned."
    - "Text auto-resize is not set to HEIGHT or WIDTH_AND_HEIGHT \u2014 ContentSizeFitter
      not assigned."
    - "Parent has Auto Layout \u2014 LayoutElement.preferred* handles sizing instead
      of ContentSizeFitter."
    - "Object has no visible fills or strokes and is not a vector \u2014 Image tag
      not assigned."
    - "Object has no effects \u2014 Shadow tag not assigned."
    - Object has shadow effects, but the current framework/component does not support
      them (e.g. UITK, SpriteRenderer, UGUI without TrueShadow).
    - "Object has no effects \u2014 Blur tag not assigned."
    - Object has background blur effects, but Blur is only supported in Nova framework.
    - Object has layout grids, but DrawLayoutGrids is disabled in Main Settings.
    - "Object has no layout grids \u2014 LayoutGrid tag not assigned."
    - "Object opacity is 1.0 \u2014 CanvasGroup not needed."
    - "Object has no visible children \u2014 Container tag not assigned."
